fields.name: Possession of deadly weapons
fields.description: Possession of deadly weapons (e.g., Indian pana, ice pick, pointed comb, knives, improvised weapons)
fields.legal_references: DepEd Child Protection Policy  DepEd Order (DO) 40, s.2012; School Policy on contraband; RPC provisions on unlawful aggression may apply case-to-case.

fields.name: Use/peddling/pushing of marijuana or prohibited drugs
fields.description: Use of / peddling / pushing of marijuana or any prohibited drugs
fields.legal_references: RA 9165 (Comprehensive Dangerous Drugs Act of 2002) & DepEd's Anti-Drug policies; DO 40, s.2012 (protection/discipline procedures).

fields.name: Assaulting teacher/school personnel or physical assault
fields.description: Assaulting a teacher or school personnel; participating in unsanctioned strikes/demonstrations; inflicting injury upon another student / physical assault
fields.legal_references: RPC Art. 148 (Direct Assault) in relation to Art. 152 (teachers/personnel as persons in authority via Commonwealth Act 578); DO 40, s.2012 (violence, threats, due process). Peaceable assembly needs prior approval per School Policy.

fields.name: Theft/shoplifting/stealing
fields.description: Theft / shoplifting / stealing (in-campus or off-campus)
fields.legal_references: RPC Art. 308-310 (Theft); School Policy for administrative discipline.

fields.name: Forging/tampering of school records
fields.description: Forging / tampering of school records; misrepresentation
fields.legal_references: RPC Art. 171-172 (Falsification of documents); School Policy on academic records.

fields.name: Gross indecency in conduct
fields.description: Gross indecency in conduct (PDA; acts of lasciviousness; exhibitionism) or perennial misbehavior
fields.legal_references: School Policy / Code of Conduct; DO 40, s.2012 (protection from sexual harassment/abuse). Criminal acts, if any, fall under RPC (e.g., acts of lasciviousness).

fields.name: Organization/membership in unsanctioned groups
fields.description: Organization/membership in any fraternity, sorority, gang, or any group not sanctioned by the school
fields.legal_references: DO 7, s.2006 (Prohibition of fraternities/sororities in elementary & secondary schools); School Policy on student organizations.

fields.name: Extortion/swindling
fields.description: Extortion / swindling
fields.legal_references: RPC Art. 293-296 (Robbery with violence/intimidation); RPC Art. 315 (Estafa/Swindling); DO 40, s.2012 (bullying/harassment).

fields.name: Bullying or peer abuse
fields.description: Bullying or peer abuse
fields.legal_references: RA 10627 (Anti-Bullying Act of 2013); DO 55, s.2013 (IRR of RA 10627); DO 40, s.2012 (Child Protection Policy; Sec. 3.M definition of bullying).

fields.name: Inflicting injury upon another student
fields.description: Inflicting injury upon another student/physical assault
fields.legal_references: RPC Art. 262-266 (Physical Injuries); DO 40, s.2012 (Violence, threats); School Policy.

fields.name: Vandalism/destruction of school property
fields.description: Vandalism / intentional destruction of school property
fields.legal_references: RPC Art. 327 (Malicious Mischief); School Policy (restitution/discipline).

fields.name: Destruction of nature
fields.description: Destruction of nature (plants/trees/animals used for education)
fields.legal_references: School Policy; possible LGU Ordinance / environmental laws depending on context.

fields.name: Littering/non-observance of waste management
fields.description: Littering/scattering pieces of papers/peelings/wrappers/plastics or non-observance of waste/garbage management
fields.legal_references: RA 9003 (Ecological Solid Waste Management Act); School Policy; LGU Ordinance.

fields.name: Cheating on classwork
fields.description: Cheating on classwork
fields.legal_references: School Policy on Academic Integrity; DO 40, s.2012 (discipline due process).

fields.name: Intentional spitting on walls and railings
fields.description: Intentional spitting on walls and railings of stairs
fields.legal_references: School Policy (sanitation & conduct).

fields.name: Smoking & vaping
fields.description: Smoking & vaping (in-campus & within the 20-meter perimeter radius outside the school)
fields.legal_references: RA 9211 (Tobacco Regulation Act) & EO 26 (2017) (Smoke-Free Environments); RA 11900 (Vape Law, restricts sales/use by minors & in schools); School Policy (alcohol prohibition).

fields.name: Taking/bringing intoxicating drinks or entering under influence
fields.description: Taking and/or bringing any intoxicating drinks on campus or entering the campus under the influence of alcohol
fields.legal_references: School Policy; DO 40, s.2012 (safety and well-being provisions).

fields.name: Any form of gambling
fields.description: Any form of gambling
fields.legal_references: PD 1602 (Illegal gambling penalties); School Policy.

fields.name: Insinuating trouble or fight
fields.description: Insinuating trouble or fight
fields.legal_references: DO 40, s.2012 (violence/threats); School Policy.

fields.name: Unsafe behavior on school premises
fields.description: Sitting on railings or arms of chairs, jumping and/or sliding on stairway railings in going down, hanging on/jumping over the windows/storeys of building
fields.legal_references: School Safety Policy; DO 40, s.2012 (child protection & safety).

fields.name: Making unnecessary noise in corridors
fields.description: Shouting or making unnecessary noise while passing along lobbies or corridors
fields.legal_references: School Policy (order and discipline).

fields.name: Making derogatory statements
fields.description: Making any derogatory statements against fellow student, teacher, school personnel, administrators and visitors
fields.legal_references: DO 40, s.2012 (bullyingverbal abuse); RA 10627, if peer-to-peer; School Policy.

fields.name: Climbing over perimeter fence
fields.description: Climbing over perimeter fence in going in or out of the school premises
fields.legal_references: School Policy on safety; DO 40, s.2012 (hazardous conduct).

fields.name: Truancy/habitual absenteeism/tardiness
fields.description: Truancy/habitual absenteeism/tardiness/cutting or skipping classes
fields.legal_references: DO 8, s.2015 (Classroom Assessmentattendance expectations); School Policy.

fields.name: Unauthorized use of personal gadgets in class
fields.description: Using/playing of personal gadgets while the class is going on (unless allowed by the teacher for educational purposes, and for emergency cases)
fields.legal_references: School Policy on electronic device use; DO 40, s.2012 (classroom discipline).

fields.name: Possession/showing of pornographic materials
fields.description: Possession and/or showing of pornographic materials (printed or digital)
fields.legal_references: PD 969 / PD 960 (Obscenity Laws); RA 7610 (child protectionpornography); DO 40, s.2012; School Policy.

fields.name: Bringing and igniting firecrackers
fields.description: Bringing and igniting fire crackers in the school premises
fields.legal_references: RA 7183 (Regulation of Firecrackers); School Policy.

fields.name: School I.D. violation
fields.description: School I.D. violation such as: tampering; wearing the ID without/or having different picture; wearing a different I.D. or different cord and color, wearing of I.D. with sticker or other accessories
fields.legal_references: School Policy; DO 32, s.2003 (Student discipline guidelinesID part of uniform compliance).

fields.name: Hurling stones/materials over fence
fields.description: Hurling stones and/or any other materials over the perimeter fence
fields.legal_references: RPC Art. 327 (Malicious Mischief); School Policy; DO 40, s.2012 (violent/risky conduct).

fields.name: Prohibited games on campus
fields.description: Playing billiards online & offline games during school hours. Playing kick, badminton, and other ball games on campus is allowed with restrictions. However Games that may cause property or pose a risk to other learners are prohibited inside classroom, along corridors in hallways, near office, parking areas, pathways, and gardens. The designated venues for ballgames are the old covered court (OCC) in the oval field.
fields.legal_references: School Policy on conduct and safety; DO 40, s.2012 (child protection & safe environment).

fields.name: Improper haircut (male students)
fields.description: Maintain regular and clean haircuts for male student
fields.legal_references: DepEd Order No. 46, s. 2008, item No.4, Clearly Stipulates that: "4. Promoting physical hygiene and proper school decorum is part of the teaching-learning process in school, thus a student's attire and physical appearance should manifest learnings from this process."

fields.name: Excessive makeup/colored nail polish

fields.legal_references: DepEd Order No. 46, s. 2008, item No.4, Clearly Stipulates that: "4. Promoting physical hygiene and proper school decorum is part of the teaching-learning process in school, thus a student's attire and physical appearance should manifest learnings from this process."

fields.name: Wearing caps inside classroom

fields.name: LGBTQA+ Non-compliance with uniform/hairstyle

fields.legal_references: DepEd Order No. 32, s. 2017, Gender-Responsive Basic Education Policy, IV.i clearly stipulates that: i. A person's gender expressions may not be consistent with socially prescribed gender roles and may or may not reflect his or her gender identity
